sentences.english: County-level cities have both urban and rural dual characteristics.
sentences.chinese: 县级市兼有城市和农村的双重特性。

sentences.english: Shouguang, a county-level city, is China's largest vegetable production base.
sentences.chinese: 县级市寿光是我国目前最大的蔬菜种植基地。

sentences.english: Hunchun is a county-level city in Yanji Korean Autonomous Prefecture in Jilin Province.
sentences.chinese: 珲春市隶属于延边朝鲜族自治州的县级市。

sentences.english: A county would often have a subbranch of the bank.
sentences.chinese: 通常情况下，县级市只设立中国银行支行。

sentences.english: Why can a small prefectural class town have so great charm?
sentences.chinese: 一个小小的县级市为什么会有如此大的魅力？

sentences.english: It is the first county-level city affiliated customs within the jurisdictions of Hangzhou Customs.
sentences.chinese: 这是杭州海关关区内首个设立在县级市的隶属海关。

definition: subprovincial city (having independent economic status within a province)
sub-prefecture-level city (county level division, administered by province, not under a prefecture)
administrative unit (e.g. province 省[sheng3], prefecture 地區|地区[di4 qu1] or county 縣|县[xian4])
municipality, namely: Beijing 北京, Tianjin 天津, Shanghai 上海 and Chongqing 重慶|重庆, the first level administrative subdivision/province level city/also called directly governed city
to govern/to control/having jurisdiction over/linchpin of a wheel (archaic)/noise of a barrow
direct management of a county by the province (PRC administrative reform)
